24/06/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- President Stipe Mesic bestowed the High Order of King Tomislav with Ribbon and Great Danica on visiting Albanian counterpart Alfred Moisiu, during a ceremony on Saturday (June 23rd). Both presidents stressed that their states share common goals of EU and NATO membership and hope for the transformation of Southeast Europe into a region of peace, security and stability. Moisiu was attending the regional energy forum in Zagreb. (HRT, Albanian President website - 23/06/07)
